  "description": "Mint/labiate family — ~236 genera, ~7,200 species. Diagnostic square stems, opposite leaves, bilabiate (two-lipped) flowers, aromatic essential oils in glandular trichomes. Includes basil, oregano, rosemary, sage, mint, thyme, lavender; major culinary and medicinal importance.",
